\section{Shared semantics}{

Whatever the class, the same rules hold:
\itemize{
\item A robust \code{vcov} request is honoured through the class's
field-standard backend, or \strong{refused with a clear error} naming the
supported set -- never silently ignored, and the footer always names
the estimator actually applied.
\item \code{exponentiate = TRUE} is link-gated: it produces a labelled ratio
(OR / IRR / HR / RR / MR / RRR / TR) only where the link warrants
one; identity-link fits warn and are left untouched.
\item Class-specific structure renders as labelled subordinate blocks
of rows in the same table (ordinal \code{Thresholds}, mixed
\verb{Random effects}, two-part \code{Zero-inflation} / \verb{Zero hurdle} /
\code{Dispersion}), with a footer line explaining each block.
\item Fit statistics default to the family's field standard and can be
overridden with \code{show_fit_stats}; class-inappropriate tokens are
rejected with a pointer to the right ones.
\item Everything is available programmatically: \code{broom::tidy()},
\code{glance()}, \code{\link[=as_structured]{as_structured()}}, \code{as.data.frame()}.
}
